</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
Stats generated by Neill's parser.<br>
<br>
Not quite sure what to make of this. My evade rate apparently increases slightly, but it's pretty insignificant. And my parry rate drops by 5%... Some odd data. I'll try a longer test with the cleric buffed in a day or two, see if having a higher weaponskill gives a better result (though the reason for the low WS was to inflate the numbers so that differences would be easier to spot). <p>----<br>
Danya, 50 Mercenary, Prydwen<br>
Danyan, 50 Minstrel, Prydwen<br>
Danya, 50 Mentalist, Excalibur</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mercenary Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 711<br> <font color=#000000>(10/11/03 8:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=368.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another post that proves Evade I doesn't scale</span><hr size=1> If your Evade rate increases your Parry rate is likely to drop because Evade is checked first. (Evade/Parry/Block)  Given that the difference is only 1.6% and the Miss rate changed by 2% (which shouldn't have changed at all, in theory) I'd be just as likely to believe that it's just a RNG fluke.  It'd be nice to try this out sometime with a MUCH larger sample (500+, preferably 1000+ attacks), that way RNG streakiness is lessened.  I would surely hope that nearly doubling Dex and Qui would have a MUCH larger effect than that. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
&lt;The Kindred&gt;<br>
Gawaine<br>
50 Saracen Slash Merc</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#000000>(10/11/03 10:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=368.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another post that proves Evade I doesn't scale</span><hr size=1> &quot;He didn't do a test with and another test without buffs so you can't draw any conclusions about evade rates. The unbuffed evade rate might have been 1% for all we know. &quot;<br>
